tors' Foreword lays out the historical and cultural context for the undertaking. Ousterhout and Jackson recount the lives and careers of the two authors and the tale of their collaboration on the excavation and subsequent book.Publication of this volume was supported by a grant from the Joukowsky Family Foundation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aArchitecture, Early ChristianzTurkeyzKonya. 0aChristian antiquitieszTurkey. 0aChurch architecturezTurkeyzKonya. 4aReligious Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Archaeology.2bisacsh  aArchaeology.  aReligious Studies.1 aBell, Gertrude L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aJackson, Mark P. C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJackson, Mark P. C., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOusterhout, Robert G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOusterhout, Robert G., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRAMSAY, W. M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package Complete Collectionz978311041345808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package Social Sciencesz978311041361808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311045954840uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/978193453630840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781934536308423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781934536308.jpg  a978-3-11-041345-8  Penn Press eBook Package Complete Collection  a978-3-11-041361-8  Penn Press eBook Package Social Sciences  a978-3-11-045954-8  University of Pennsylvania Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_E